<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_design_to_individual  Attribute: product_design 
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual.product_design"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual.product_design">
the design of the product that is being made.
</ext_description>

  <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_design_to_individual  Informal proposition: IP1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual.wr:IP1">
     <p>
       The 
       <express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>
       which the individual is an instance of is the same as the 
       <express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>
       of which the design is a 
       <express_ref
         linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>.
     </p>
     <note>
       Using a mapping like syntax, this can be written as:
     </note>
     <screen>
    &#160;{<express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/> -&gt; <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/> 
    &#160;&#160;<express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/> &lt;= <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>
    &#160;&#160;<express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version.of_product">Product_version.of_product</express_ref>-&gt;<express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>
    &#160;&#160;<express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product.id">Product.id</express_ref> = X1}
    &#160;AND
    &#160;{<express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/>-&gt;<express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>
    &#160;&#160;<express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version.of_product">Product_version.of_product</express_ref>-&gt;<express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>
    &#160;&#160;<express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product.id">Product.id</express_ref> = X2}
    &#160;AND
    &#160;{X1 = X2}
  </screen>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_as_individual_version  
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual_version"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual_version">
  <p>
    A <b>Product_as_individual_version</b> is a type of 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>.
    It is a revision of a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>
    and acts as a collector of the definitions of this revision.
  </p>

  <example number="1"> 
  <p>
    The car on my drive is represented by a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>.
    The current configuration status of the car can be represented by a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>
    related to the 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>.
    If a safety modification is made to the car resulting in a new
    configuration status of the car, then this may be represented by
    a new 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>.
  </p>
  </example>

  <example number="2">
    <p>
      HMS Daring is the first of a new class of  ships known as Type 45
      Destroyers. It is due to enter service in two years time.   
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The version of the generic Type 45 ship design that applies to HMS
        Daring is represented by a 
        <express_ref 
          linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>;
      </li>
      <li>
        The ship HMS Daring is represented by a
        <express_ref
          linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>.
        This identifies the planned ship, and when built, the actual ship;
      </li>
      <li>
        The planned revision of the future ship HMS Daring is represented by a 
        <express_ref
          linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>
        related back to the  
        <express_ref
          linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>;
      </li>
      <li>
        When built, the first revision the actual ship, HMS  Daring will be represented by a
        <express_ref
          linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>. 
      </li>
    </ul>
  </example>

</ext_description>
